# Security

## Environment Variables
- All Firebase config via `REACT_APP_*` (e.g. `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_API_KEY`)
- Never commit `.env` or `.env.local`; use `.env.example` as template
- Required vars: `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_API_KEY`, `AUTH_DOMAIN`, `PROJECT_ID`, `STORAGE_BUCKET`, `MESSAGING_SENDER_ID`, `APP_ID`, `MEASUREMENT_ID`

## Sensitive Data
- No API keys, tokens, or passwords in source code
- No `console.log` of credentials or PII in production builds
- Remove debug logging of env vars before production (see initFirebase.js)

## Auth & Authorisation
- Admin/developer actions: verify `userData.admin` or `userData.developer` server-side where possible
- Firestore rules must enforce auth; client checks are UX only
- Use Firebase Auth for all auth; no custom JWT/session logic

## Input Validation
- Validate and sanitise user input before Firestore writes
- Use Firestore rules to reject invalid document shapes
